RAG : Usually while llm model tries to answer the solution it is tough that the answer should be from trained data or related to it
   If not it tries to hallucinates the answers....
So we use RAG to reduce hallucinations and answer in documents we choose 
There are many types of RAG

Traditional Rag : this system where taking the documents find the relevent chunk nd answer

Advanced RAG : It solves the problem of irrelevant generation...After it gets the related context it tries to rerank also one more is like it tries to rewrite the query given by user to make it more accurate
this is where we use chunking,embedding for getting the semantic relations also

Hybrid: It is a mix where it gets the relevent and also the semantic context(mostly used)
  Keyword search (BM25)
+
Vector search (Embeddings)

Agentic RAG:this is advanced where the agent tries to choose the defination
Agent decides:
• what to retrieve
• when to retrieve
• which tool to use
• how many steps to take
There are many ways to implement the rag 
langchain                         HAYSTACK                   DSPY     
HAYSTACK is mostly used for entriprisal usages
DSPY is more advanced research done by standfords and no need to query rewriting asthe model can rewrite it is automated
DSPy automatically optimizes prompts and reasoning pipelines.

